The relative usefulness of internal opinion polls.
Will internal opinion polls - such as the questionnaire presented to Orange employees - contribute to a revolution in management practices?
I'm afraid not.
Mainly because I've already seen for myself that in the face of a new situation, the structure after different turns returns preferably to what it always did!
And because authoritarianism, as one of the pathologies of power, increases in proportion to the severity of one's own failures.
And finally, because most executives have a simplified view of human behavior.
Because they're graduates of engineering colleges, they have a mechanical interpretation of psychology.
For the sake of intellectual convenience, they adopt an old behaviorist theory, now revived by the US neuroscientists and widely disseminated without much knowledge by the scientific establishment and the media.
With the "levers" (sic) of managers' involvement, a recent Ipsos survey on Figaro.fr showed that it only confirms managers in their position of mechanical control, unsuitable for today's world.
Identify and measure the mobilisation factors.
