The Turkish judiciary has dissolved the Kurdish side and this decision has serious consequences.
Turkey's Constitutional Court on Friday ruled to abolish the country's main pro-Kurdish party, a decision that prompted protests and demonstrations in the Kurdish community in the southeast and in Istanbul.
