The night visions are rather depressing.
When she waits in her dark room for sleep, which rarely comes and is too late, she often cannot tell whether she is awake or asleep, whether the images she sees, the grimaces, or the girl with the bleeding cut wounds on her hands and feet, are coming before her eyes open or closed.
Leave me alone, he's yelling at the characters.
She doesn't tell her parents or friends, they'd think she was crazy.
In the fall of 2009, Sarah K. turns 20 today.
